It
was
a
concern
which
brought
just
employment
enough.
He
had
still
a
small
house
in
Highbury,
where
most
of
his
leisure
days
were
spent;
and
between
useful
occupation
and
the
pleasures
of
society,
the
next
eighteen
or
twenty
years
of
his
life
passed
cheerfully
